public Term getReplacement(LogicalVariable substituted)
Returns the replacement of a given logical variable in this substitution.

For instance, if the substitution is given by the set {X/Y, Z/r}, then calling this method with the parameter 'X' will return the logical variable 'Y'.

hasCommonReplacement

public boolean hasCommonReplacement(LogicalVariable firstVariable,
                                    LogicalVariable secondVariable)
Returns true if the specified logical variables have the same replacement in this substitution. That is, if the specified variables are X and Y, this method returns true if there is a term t such that X/t and Y/t are both in this substitution.
If such term is not found, or if one or both logical variables have no replacements in this substitution, this method returns false.

Parameters:
firstVariable - The first variable to compare
secondVariable - The second variable to compare
Returns:
True if the specified logical variables have a common replacement, false otherwise.

isUnifier

public boolean isUnifier(Prv prv1,
                         Prv prv2)
Returns true if this substitution unifies the specified Prv

A substitution θ is a unifier of two parameterized random variables f (ti1,...,tik ) and f(tj1,...,tjk) if f(ti1,...,tik)[θ] = f(tj1,...,tjk)[θ].

We then say that the two parameterized random variables unify [Kisynski, 2010].

Parameters:
prv1 - The first Prv.
prv2 - The second Prv.
Returns:
true if this substitution the specified PRVs, false otherwise.
